description: Welcome to a charming colonial home nestled on a pretty neighborhood street. This home has hardwood floors, and a bonus den off the kitchen.  Tear off roof is brand new from July of 2020, and furnace is 10 years old.  Come see this home and all it has to offer.  Delayed showings on September 3, 2020 at noon. Delayed negotiations September 8th at 2pm.

Charming 1513 sqft 2 story colonial in Irondequoit! Beautiful hardwoods, this home has no shortage of allure. The interior is very inviting w/cozy living room featuring decorative fireplace! The spacious eat-in kitchen features stainless steel appliances and tons of natural light. The second floor houses 3 large bedrooms! Spacious deck off of the kitchen, and fully fenced yard. Great for entertaining! Beautiful formal dining room. Convenient to Webster shopping! Upgrades include: new furnace in 2016.

What a deal! With a little work, this will be a great money maker. Up is vacant and ready for your personal touches. Down tenant is long term. Vinyl Siding. Hardwood Flooring. Newer High Efficiency Furnaces. Roof is near end of life but no leaks reported. Due to COVID-19, tenant, property and Certificate of Occupancy (just expired) are "as is". All offers must reflect this. Do not wait! Rates are at an all time low as is housing inventory.

Welcome to this charming two bedroom home on a quiet neighborhood street.  Lovely Updated kitchen, spacious living room, formal dining room with slider to rear deck and fenced in yard.  Home needs very little  TLC consisting of fresh paint and carpet.  Enclosed front porch for your enjoyment, Brand new water service into the home, roof only 5 yrs old. Appliances stay.  Electric garage door opener, vinyl windows, Great starter home Ready to move in for the holiday!  Schedule your showing today!!  NO DELAYS

Come check out this East Irondequoit beauty! The main floor offers an open flowing floor plan with a large eat in kitchen and dinning/living room combo. First floor office or den. New paint throughout the home. Upstairs you will find 3 generous sized bedrooms with plenty of closet space and new carpet throughout. The newly renovated bathroom will not disappoint. The garage is currently added living space but can be easily converted back to garage space by removing a wall. Schedule your private tour today!

Well maintained Colonial in the historic Homestead Heights Neighborhood! This home sits on a quiet street minutes from Downtown Rochester. Features include vinyl replacement windows, fully fenced in backyard, Architectural roof (2 years old), original hardwood floors, upgraded electrical panel (200 AMPS), glass block basement windows, original gum wood trim throughout, crown molding, open concept living/dining room, enclosed front porch, two car detached garage. Lots of natural light, full attic with stair access that could be finished if desired. Seller is willing to leave behind the following items should the buyer have a need for them: (lawnmower, weed eater, snowblower, lawn tools, drapes, AC window unit). Average RG&E $125/month. Delayed negotiations until Monday 9/21/20 at 3 pm.

Welcome to this updated Colonial home on tree lined neighborhood street. Lots of charm, some natural woodwork, gum wood trim, and original hardwoods. Living room has a triple window letting the light in. There is a decorative brick fireplace and leaded glass bookcases on both sides. There is an arched doorway to the dining room.  The kitchen has been updated. Newer appliances, gas stove, microwave  SS sink. There is an enclosed front porch. Upstairs 3 bedrooms and full bath. Full bath in basement. 2 car detached garage. Freshly painted, cleaned and move in ready.

Full attic that can be finished and used for additional living space or used for storage. Brand new tear off roof in 2017, new water tank in 2015. All offers due by Tuesday September 1st at 3pm.

Charming 3 bedroom, 1.5 bath Colonial.  Wonderful open concept floor plan with the formal dining room connecting the living room and spacious family room.  Updated kitchen with oak cabinets and stainless steel appliances. Beautiful hardwood floors in family room, dining room and upstairs. Amazing primary bedroom with great closet space, along with two nice size additional bedrooms.   Fresh paint throughout (2017), new bathroom vanity (2017), Hot water tank (2013), Tear off Roof (2009). Fantastic semi-private partially fenced backyard. One car attached garage with electric garage door opener.  You won't want to miss this one! Don't forget to check out the video tour!
